text: It was naturally a highly popular victory with the Londoners, but it brought heavy. censure from nobles who still believed that they had a monopoly of leadership. But, at last, Gaunt sailed. Opposing him was the French Admiral, Jean de Vienne- a great sailor and an able strategist.
